🧪 Test Suite — Product Spec Linter
Tests live in tests/test_linter.py. Run with:
pip install pytest
pytest tests/ -v

Test Coverage
#	Test	Rule(s)	What it validates
1	Single word input	COMPLETENESS	Rejected before LLM call — no API cost
2	Empty string	AMBIGUITY, MISSING_AC	Rejected before LLM call
3	Word count boundary (14 vs 15)	AMBIGUITY	Exact threshold enforcement
4	Clean minimal story	AMBIGUITY	Zero findings for a well-written story
5	Ambiguous language	AMBIGUITY	ERROR + WARNING parsed correctly
6	Missing acceptance criteria	MISSING_AC	ERROR with Given/When/Then suggestion
7	Internal contradiction	CONTRADICTION	conflict_with field populated
8	Schema change blast radius	DEPENDENCY_GAP	Service impact analysis detected
9	Large multi-layer story	COMPLETENESS	Split recommendation with ready Jira stories
10	Multi-rule realistic story	All rules	Summary counts accurate across 5 rules

Design Principles
•	No real LLM calls — all tests use MockBackend for speed and cost-free CI
•	Deterministic — mock responses are hardcoded, tests never flake
•	Structural + semantic — tests validate both JSON structure and content quality
•	Boundary-focused — edge cases (empty, min-length, max-complexity) are explicit test cases
Adding New Tests
def test_11_your_new_case():
    backend = MockBackend('{"findings": [...]}')
    linter = PRDLinter(backend)
    result = linter.lint(YOUR_STORY, enabled_rules=["RULE"])
    assert result["summary"]["ERROR"] == expected_count

